Losing a 3 set battle, 16-18 to get to the finals is what we remember most. Yes, we played some of our best volleyball, as a team and individually, and it was a level good enough to get our names on the pier. Unfortunately it didn’t happen, and in sport that’s what we remember most. We remember the last few points of our semis game where we didn’t execute perfectly and it cost us the match, and that freaking sucks! Sure we will bounce back, and learn, and grow but I’m not going to sugar coat it…it sucks and I’d give just about anything for a do-over.

Let the journey begin. Boxing.

Great job @estock2 I love nothing more than training ELITE level athletes. These types of athletes already understand the importance of hard work and they don’t shy away from it. These athletes know what it will take to get them to where they want to go! Talent is everywhere, but work ethic is not 🇺🇸 #TEAMUSA 
+
I do very little mitt work when I’m starting with an athlete from the ground up. The majority of what we do is shadow boxing, drilling and bag work. When an athlete can apply what they’ve learned on the bag (on their own) that is how I know they are understanding what they are learning! It is easy for the coach to “lead the dance” because we are guiding the boxer step-by-step. Coaches: do not overlook the importance of bag work! The mitts are for fun and for sharpening the tools in their toolbox! #lahabraboxingclub
